==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sot
<hw>Sot</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. LL.
<ets>sottus</ets>; of unknown origin, cf. Ir. <ets>sotal</ets> pride,
<ets>soithir</ets> proud, or Chald. & NHeb. <ets>shoten</ets>
foolish.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A stupid person; a blockhead; a dull
fellow; a dolt.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>outh.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In Egypt oft has seen the <qex>sot</qex> bow down,⟦br⟧
And reverence some d<?/ified baboon.</q> <rj><qau>Oldham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person stupefied by excessive drinking; an
habitual drunkard.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A brutal <xex>sot</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Granville.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Every sign⟦br⟧
That calls the staring <qex>sots</qex> to nasty wine.</q>
<rj><qau>Roscommon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sot</ent>⟦br⟧

