HEADWORD: Sot
<hw>Sot</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Sottish; foolish; stupid;
dull.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Rich, but <xex>sot</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Marston.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sot</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Sot
<hw>Sot</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To stupefy; to infatuate; to
besot.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I hate to see a brave, bold fellow <qex>sotted</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

